@NODE "dbpath" "Path of Databases ..."
@TOC "prefs"
@NEXT "prefs"
@PREV "prefs"

 @{b} DBPATH @{ub} is the path, where FFDS save/load the databases.
 Each Database contain the listing of one volume.
 @{i} Warning ! @{ui} If there is not enough space to save the database
 the database won`t be copied.

 @{" Change path ... " rx "ffds:rexx/change_dbpath.rexx"}

@{JCENTER} @{" RETURN to Preferences " link "prefs"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "packer" "XPK - Compressor ..."
@TOC "prefs"
@NEXT "prefs"
@PREV "prefs"

 @{b} PACKER @{ub} is the name of the XPK compressor. If you don`t
 want to compress you Databases, you choose the xpkNONE.library.
 If PACKER is NONE you don`t need the xpk-system at all.

 @{i}@{b} WARNING !!! @{ui}@{ub} If you change the this variable you`ve
 to UPDATE ALL DATABASES !

 @{" Change packer ...  " rx "ffds:rexx/change_packer.rexx"}

 @{" Set packer to NONE " rx "ffds:rexx/none_packer.rexx"}


 Requirements: a complete installed xpk package and `xpk` in a valid
               DOS path (like c:).

@{JCENTER} @{" RETURN to Preferences " link "prefs"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "search" "Text searcher ..."
@TOC "prefs"
@NEXT "prefs"
@PREV "prefs"

 @{b} SEARCH @{ub} contains the Textsearcher of FFDS. There are two
 arguments, which have to be in the command line:
  1. $dtb	This is the FROM argument. FFDS set this argument to
		the temp. database.
  2. $pat	This is the SEARCH argument. FFDS set this argument to
                the given search-pattern.
 @{i} Warning ! @{ui} The Textsearcher has to be in the official DOS-command
  searchpath (like c: etc.).


 @{" Change Textsearcher ... " rx "ffds:rexx/change_search.rexx"}


 Example: search from $dtb search $pat


@{JCENTER} @{" RETURN to Preferences " link "prefs"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "viewer" "Text viewer ..."
@TOC "prefs"
@NEXT "prefs"
@PREV "prefs"

 @{b} VIEW @{ub} contains the Textviewer of FFDS. The $rst argument is the
 FILE argument. FFDS set this argument to the resultfile of the search

 @{i} Warning ! @{ui} The Textviewer has to be in the official DOS-command
  searchpath (like c: etc.).


 @{" Change Textviewer ... " rx "ffds:rexx/change_view.rexx"}


 Example: multiview $rst screen


@{JCENTER} @{" RETURN to Preferences " link "prefs"}

@ENDNODE
